{"key":"post-5340499","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>5340499</id>\n<content>Leave the weight off for the first ten minutes after it starts to shoot steam out.  Then, put the weight on and when it begins to rattle, turn the heat down so a bit of steam escapes, but the weight very rarely rattles.  Since you don't know the pressure, better let it go for a full hour once it's up to pressure for 1/2 pint jars.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>5396325</next>\n<prev>5339851</prev>\n<first>5339812</first>\n<last>5398007</last>\n<when>1140973917</when>\n<utime>02/26/06 07:11 PM</utime>\n</post>"}